The final smelting process — turning alumina into aluminum by heating it up to more than 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit and then chemically separating out the material that will become metal — is extraordinarily energy-intensive. news.headline: Oracle Faces Rising Debt Risk as Morgan Stanley Flags Credit Market Concerns
news.summary: Five-year credit-default swap costs climbed to 1.25 percentage points in November. Morgan Stanley said the rapid increase in borrowing has prompted more investors to hedge exposure.
news.article_text:
This article first appeared on GuruFocus.

Oracle (ORCL, Financials) is drawing increased scrutiny in credit markets as borrowing tied to its artificial intelligence and data-center buildout accelerates. Analysts at Morgan Stanley said five-year credit-default swap costs climbed to 1.25 percentage points in November, the highest since 2022, and could move above 1.5 points next year without more detail on the company's long-term funding strategy.

news.headline: Zscaler Slides Despite Strong Quarter
news.summary: Zscaler (NASDAQ:ZS) shares slid about 6% even though the company just posted a strong quarter and raised its outlook. Zscaler earned $0.96 per share on revenue of $788.1 million, beating forecasts.
news.article_text:
This article first appeared on GuruFocus.

Zscaler (NASDAQ:ZS) shares slid about 6% even though the company just posted a strong quarter and raised its outlook, a classic case of Wall Street shrugging at good news.

For the quarter ending Oct. 31, Zscaler earned $0.96 per share on revenue of $788.1 million, beating forecasts of $0.86 and $773.9 million. Sales jumped 26% from a year earlier, a clear sign that businesses are still investing in cybersecurity even as other tech spending slows.
